{"lemma":"فاتِحَة","slug":"فاتِحَة","root":"ف.ت.ح","root_slug":"ف-ت-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32875","n32890"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%90%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"start, beginning, commencement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"preface, preamble, introduction"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of فَاتِح (fātiḥ)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the feminine form of active participle of the verb فَتَحَ (fataḥa)."},"ipa":["/faː.ti.ħa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32875","headword_ar":"فاتحهُ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He addressed him first"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuluwku laA tufaAtaHu biAlkalaAmi","text_ar":"المُلُوكُ لَا تُفَاتَحُ بِالكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Kings shall not be addressed first with speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  And, (A, K, * TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufaAtaHapN","text_ar":"مُفَاتَحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitaAHN","text_ar":"فِتَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He commenced a dispute, debate, discussion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"controversy, with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he summoned him to the judge, and litigated with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, * TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAtHhu","text_ar":"فاتحهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bargained with him and gave him nothing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the case of his giving him, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAtkhu","text_ar":"فاتكهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA; and O and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ftk","text_ar":"فتك"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAtH","text_ar":"فاتح"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He compressed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) his wife. (TA.) ―         -b5-  [Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rendered"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-  and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was liberal."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Freytag, from the Deewán of the Hudhalees.)]"}],"source_refs":["TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n32890","headword_ar":"فَاتِحَةٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: (S, A, * K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAtiHu","text_ar":"فَوَاتِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtiHapu","text_ar":"فَاتِحَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtiHapu AlquroA=ni","text_ar":"فَاتِحَةُ القُرْا=نِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [and simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaAtiHapu","text_ar":"الفَاتِحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The opening chapter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exordium, of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is [said to be] so called because the recitation in prayer is commenced therewith. (Msb.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^a faAtiHapa","text_ar":"قَرَاَ فَاتِحَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uwrapi waxaAtimatahaA","text_ar":"السُّورَةِ وَخَاتِمَتَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He recited the first part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of the chapter of the Kur-án and its last part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAtiHu AlquroA=ni","text_ar":"فَوَاتِحُ القُرْا=نِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first parts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions, of the chapters of the Kur-án."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufotataHN","text_ar":"مُفْتَتَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA"]}]}}